</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="231" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,834,1003]" pageId="10" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,942,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="231">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species was only reported from mangrove habitats and is probably endemic to the Galápagos Islands (
<bibRefCitation box="[245,525,978,1003]" pageId="10" pageNumber="231" refId="ref10382" refString="Niedbala, W. &amp; Schatz, H. (1996) Euptyctimous mites from the Galapagos Islands, Cocos Island, and Central America (Acari: Oribatida). Genus, 7, 239 - 317." type="journal article">Niedbała &amp; Schatz 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
